{"title":"Fox Racing’s Union Boa Goes Flat","link":"https://theradavist.com/fox-racings-union-boa-goes-flat/","date":1711466667000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2181\" height=\"1454\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?fit=1200,1454&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?w=2181&amp;quality=75 2181w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/FoxRacingUnionBoaFlat.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>The only shoes <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/fox-racing-union-boa-clipless-shoes-review/\" target=\"_blank\">John reviewed last year</a>, the Fox Racing Union Boa Clipless, just got a few makeover option as a flat pedal. The Union Boa Flat ($224.95) is identical to the clipless model but comes in a grippy flat sole for flat pedals. After heavy use, John’s still a fan of these shoes. Check out more at <a href=\"https://www.foxracing.com/product/fox-union-boa-flat/32820.html\" target=\"_blank\">Fox Racing</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/fox-racings-union-boa-goes-flat/\">Fox Racing’s Union Boa Goes Flat</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"d4dce3208d07ede8e41715edeb6ef57319bc9e08b8ec63a6bee037fb67438082","category":"Cycling"}